          <physDesc>
            <p>Vellum, about 11 in. by 7 1/8, consisting of 108 leaves, the first two of which are slightly torn. The quires were originally 12 in number, but the last is now missing. They are signed with both letters and arithmetical figures (e. g. fol 61, %; fol. 71, %).  Each page is divided into two columns, of from 38 to 42 lines. This volume is written in a fine, regular Esṭrangĕlā of the viith cent., with with the exception of fol. <locus from="81">81</locus>, which is a later restoration.</p>
